channel.title: New Runescape Interface
channel.description:
Well, Jagex has just updated the interface [b]completely[/b]. Go take a look at it for yourself. I'm assuming this will mess up a lot of the SRL procedures. Like finding game tabs, setting to run, a lot of things. I'm guessing there's going have to be a new version of SRL?
So what do you guys think about this?
P.S. I'd watch any scripts you run, just incase the interface messes em up, because it probably will :rolleyes:.
-Weibs.
EDIT: I was reading through, and found out a few other things.
A lumby bank. New tutors in lumby. New sounds. The way the signposts work. Free teleport to new chars. A cross way to alkharid from lumby swamp, if you have a crossbow.

item.title: New Runescape Interface
item.dc:creator: @Weibs Weibs
item.description:
@Weibs wrote:

Lol, its not that amazing, I’d say the “coolest” new feature is the sounds, like birds chirping, bubbling fountains, waterfalls growing louder as you get closer, but thats not that great either.

But one thing that is actually a good thing for us, is the new free teleport to Lumby. Although, you can only use it every 30 mins, but say, if a script gets lost, instead of logging out, it could tele to lumby, and then start over from there.

And you can get a free sword and shield from the melee tutor, and then either some arrows every 30 mins from the range tutor, or some runes every 30 mins from the mage tutor.

item.title: New Runescape Interface
item.dc:creator: @PaulT PaulT
item.description:
@PaulT wrote:

I'm sure jagex are well aware that it would affect autoers somewhat, but it really isn't a huge deal from our perspective, just a little annoying.

Good points. I agree update is mostly for aesthetics and function, not to deter people from cheating. I don’t play Runescape, so I don’t know if they have added things like viewing your FPS, what world you’re on, your ping, etc., but it’s a travesty if they haven’t. It’s the lack of basic production values that pisses people off the most about the Runescape experience, and updates like this help.

Edit: Just played with the new update a bit, and looks like they’ve changed a bit more than they’ve actually said, mostly visual stuff, but there’s some gameplay mechanics that have been tweaked as well.

Read full topic

item.title: New Runescape Interface
item.dc:creator: @Boreas Boreas
item.description:
@Boreas wrote:

I think updating scripts will be a bigger problem than updating srl.
Due to the way srl is organized, it can be updated fairly quickly. Due to the way noobs and leechs are, they won’t catch on that quick and will try to auto and fail. This will only be a short decrease in autoers. (maybe the noobs and leeches will get banned) The only way this could be a big problem is if huge interface updates like this happened all the time, which is impractical for the rs devs and legit players wouldn’t stand for it.

Theres alot of good changes from a players perspective (like having the auto retailate in the fighting section and othe logical ‘why didn’t they do that before’ type stuff), so they can justify the changes and only piss off players for a little bit while they get used to it. I’m sure jagex are well aware that it would affect autoers somewhat, but it really isn’t a huge deal from our perspective, just a little annoying.

Read full topic
